<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-01-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-01-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="479" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d479">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 10901/1.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Russian Ambassador</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-01-07"><hi rend="italic">January 7,
                                1908</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 59.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: In compliance with the request
                            contained in your note of the 7th instant, and in pursuance of existing
                            treaty stipulations between the United States and Russia, I have the
                            honor to transmit this department’s certificate, stating that the
                            Government of Russia has requested the extradition of Jan Janov Pouren,
                            alias W. Kohks, alias Martin Martinson, charged with murder, robbery and
                            attempt at murder in Russia, and a fugitive from its justice in the
                            United States. Accept, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Elihu Root.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>